To install libsdl2-dev on Linux, you can follow these steps:

Open a terminal window.

Enter the command sudo apt-get install libsdl2-dev and press Enter.
    
Enter your password when prompted and press Enter.
   
Wait for the installation process to complete.

Note that the specific steps for installing libsdl2-dev may vary depending on your Linux distribution. For example, Red Hat-based systems (including Fedora) can simply do sudo dnf install SDL2-devel to get headers and other build requirements ready for compiling your own SDL programs2

Gentoo users can sudo emerge libsdl2 to get everything they need2
 
If you encounter any issues during installation, you can refer to online forums and communities for help1

